cs.LO, cs.LG, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a new approach to learning automata using logical formulas as tests. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as automata learning is a popular technique in machine learning. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of logical formulas as tests, which is a common technique in programming language semantics. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses learning labelled transition systems, which are commonly used in software engineering for modelling system behaviour. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses learning automata, which is a core topic in this sub-category.
